## Maintainer reply

Hi @Weissger 
You're right `uri` will always be validated before. So it's a good idea to overwrite the default value to `None` and then you can use [`root_validator`](https://pydantic-docs.helpmanual.io/usage/validators/#root-validators) to set the real default value.
I would do something like this

```python
from pydantic import BaseModel, root_validator


class ModelA(BaseModel):
    uri: str = ...

class ModelB(ModelA):
    uri: str = None
    foo: str = ...
    bar: str = "a"

    @root_validator
    def set_default_uri(cls, values):
        if values['uri'] is None:
            values['uri'] = f"{values['foo']}#{values['bar']}"
        return values


print(ModelB(foo='qwe').dict())
