## Maintainer reply

Unfortunately this isn't currently possible. The reason validators have to be class methods is because the `validate_model` method (which does the meat of validation) has no access to the model instance.

You should use your approach in the first "beers" method above. If that doesn't work, this might be fixed better with "computed fields" broadly described in https://github.com/samuelcolvin/pydantic/issues/935#issuecomment-555036039
